      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 15
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available is a 2002 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) featuring the 3.6L M96 flat-six powerplant equipped with VarioCam Plus for optimized valve timing and lift. This driver-focused spec includes the G96 6-speed manual transaxle, delivering power to the rear wheels with exceptional tactile feedback. The chassis remains taut, utilizing its MacPherson strut front and multi-link rear suspension geometry to provide surgical turn-in. Braking is handled by four-piston Brembo monoblock calipers over vented rotors. This example has been meticulously maintained with a recent IMS bearing retrofit and rear main seal replacement, ensuring mechanical longevity. The Arctic Silver metallic paint retains excellent luster, and the interior demonstrates the ergonomic precision expected of a Stuttgart-engineered machine.",
      "price": 29500.0,
      "reputation": 0.3,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 15
    },
    {
